16862 silly resolved     readme: '# read-chunk [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/read-chunk.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/read-chunk)\n\n> Read a chunk from a file\n\nBecause the built-in way is too much boilerplate.\n\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\n$ npm install --save read-chunk\n```\n\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\nvar readChunk = require(\'read-chunk\');\n\n// foo.txt => hello\n\nreadChunk.sync(\'foo.txt\', 1, 3);\n//=> ell\n```\n\n\n## API\n\n### readChunk(filepath, position, length, callback)\n\n#### filepath\n\nType: `string`\n\n#### position\n\nType: `number`\n\nPosition to start reading.\n\n#### length\n\nType: `number`\n\nNumber of bytes to read.\n\n#### callback(error, buffer)\n\nType: `function`\n\n\n### readChunk.sync(filepath, start, length)\n\nSame arguments as `readChunk` except the callback.\n\nReturns a buffer.\n\n\n## License\n\nMIT © [Sindre Sorhus](http://sindresorhus.com)\n',
